      "content": "I see. So it's basically using their environment as a proxy for their character. If we look at Case A again, if a guy from a suburban background had some gaps in his resume or moved around a bit, would a prosecutor still be able to use that to argue he's \"unreliable,\" or does the background handle most of the suspicion for him? It feels like there's a massive double standard in how those \"unreliability\" factors are interpreted depending on where they come from.",
