      "content": "Yes, the background acts as a shield for Case A, meaning those same minor issues are often overlooked or excused as temporary hiccups. A prosecutor would have a much harder time framing minor employment gaps as evidence of deep character flaws when the defendant comes from a stable, privileged environment. The perception of inherent trustworthiness is built into the narrative for Case A, whereas for Case B, the instability is automatically interpreted as evidence of deeper, more systemic issues. This disparity in how \"unreliability\" is perceived is a clear reflection of societal bias.",
